abstract: Jahshire Hardnett hit a 3-pointer with 2 seconds remaining for his only points of the game and Missouri-Kansas City slipped past South Dakota 78-75 on Sunday.
snippet: Jahshire Hardnett hit a 3-pointer with 2 seconds remaining for his only points of the game and Missouri-Kansas City slipped past South Dakota 78-75 on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: VERMILLION, S.D. — Jahshire Hardnett hit a 3-pointer with 2 seconds remaining for his only points of the game and Missouri-Kansas City slipped past South Dakota 78-75 on Sunday.
headline_main: Hardnett's 3 Lifts UMKC Over South Dakota 78-75
headline_print_headline: Hardnett's 3 Lifts UMKC Over South Dakota 78-75

abstract: As black players in Europe endure racist incidents with increasing regularity, striker Romelu Lukaku speaks out about what he has endured: “It’s crazy.”
snippet: As black players in Europe endure racist incidents with increasing regularity, striker Romelu Lukaku speaks out about what he has endured: “It’s crazy.”
lead_paragraph: MILAN — Romelu Lukaku was planning on a relaxing evening in front of the TV. He might now find himself playing in Italy, but he was looking forward to following the fortunes of two of his former teams in the Premier League.

abstract: Japan-based drugmaker Eisai Co's U.S. subsidiary announced on Sunday that it had received approval from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration for its insomnia treatment in adult patients.

abstract: The media has a bigger problem than liberal bias.
snippet: The media has a bigger problem than liberal bias.
lead_paragraph: John F. Harris is about as mainstream as the mainstream media gets. He spent 21 years at The Washington Post, including as its political editor. Then he became the founding editor of Politico, where he is now a columnist.

abstract: Eli Scott poured in 26 points and sophomore Ivan Alipiev added his first-career double-double to guide Loyola Marymount to a 53-46 victory over Cal State Fullerton on Sunday.
snippet: Eli Scott poured in 26 points and sophomore Ivan Alipiev added his first-career double-double to guide Loyola Marymount to a 53-46 victory over Cal State Fullerton on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Eli Scott poured in 26 points and sophomore Ivan Alipiev added his first-career double-double to guide Loyola Marymount to a 53-46 victory over Cal State Fullerton on Sunday.
headline_main: Loyola Marymount Rides Scott, Alipiev Past CS Fullerton
headline_print_headline: Loyola Marymount Rides Scott, Alipiev Past CS Fullerton

abstract: Evangelicals continue to support Trump in overwhelming numbers.
snippet: Evangelicals continue to support Trump in overwhelming numbers.
lead_paragraph: Thursday night, Christianity Today, long known as the “flagship” magazine of American evangelicalism, broke the internet with an editorial arguing for the impeachment and removal of Donald Trump from office. The piece, penned by the magazine’s outgoing editor, Mark Galli, implored evangelicals to consider the “unambiguous facts” of the impeachment case against the president, maintaining his actions not only violated the Constitution, but were also “profoundly immoral.”

abstract: Clippers forward Kawhi Leonard will sit out Sunday's game against the Oklahoma City Thunder with left knee soreness.
snippet: Clippers forward Kawhi Leonard will sit out Sunday's game against the Oklahoma City Thunder with left knee soreness.
lead_paragraph: OKLAHOMA CITY — Clippers forward Kawhi Leonard will sit out Sunday's game against the Oklahoma City Thunder with left knee soreness.
headline_main: Clippers Forward Kawhi Leonard Out vs. Thunder
headline_print_headline: Clippers Forward Kawhi Leonard Out vs. Thunder

abstract: The deaths reminded residents and officials of the dangers that still plague New York City’s streets, despite safety initiatives.
snippet: The deaths reminded residents and officials of the dangers that still plague New York City’s streets, despite safety initiatives.
lead_paragraph: It was a deadly 72 hours: One woman was killed by a truck that backed up into her; another person was struck by a private sanitation truck; a third was hit by three vehicles at once. Three other victims were over 65.
